image.altText: A man in a grey suit holds a folder of papers titled 'Budget 2024-25'

props.synopsis: The new ACT treasurer is facing an ambitious task of turning an almost billion-dollar deficit into a small surplus — and he's hoping to improve the books by $850 million in just a matter of months.

title.children: Even a weightlifter might struggle to hoist the ACT out of the economic doldrums

image.altText: A concrete building reading "Law Courts of the Australian Capital Territory", with Australian, ACT and Aboriginal flag.

props.synopsis: A Canberra doctor accused of sexually assaulting four young women will walk from custody next week, on the condition he is not left alone with any female staff or patients.

title.children: Canberra doctor accused of sexually assaulting four young women gets bail

image.altText: A close up of Clive Palmer wearing a blue business shirt in focus with green trees blurred in the background.

props.synopsis: Clive Palmer will take his fight to the in the High Court in Canberra today, as he seeks to re-register his United Australia Party (UAP) ahead of the next federal election.

title.children: Palmer locked in High Court battle to re-register United Australia Party

image.altText: Man in a blue suit and tie carrying a backpack.

props.synopsis: Sentencing submissions are heard in the NSW Supreme Court for Kristian White, the former police officer responsible for the death of great-grandmother Clare Nowland.

title.children: Court hears family's pain as ex-cop who tasered 95yo returns for sentencing

image.altText: A man in a grey suit stands in front of an ACT government backdrop

props.synopsis: ACT Treasurer Chris Steel unveils his first mid-year budget update, forced to reveal the bottom line is in a much worse position than was forecast.

title.children: ACT budget deficit blows out to almost $1 billion

image.altText: A close-up image of the bud of a cannabis plant.

props.synopsis: A recent study suggests the ACT's cannabis legislation is for the most part working as intended, but shows the majority of cannabis cultivators are engaging in illegal activity in order to grow it.

title.children: Canberra cultivators growing 'mild and modest' cannabis

image.altText: A man wearing handcuffs

props.synopsis: A convicted killer will test the limits of Queensland's 'no body, no parole' law in the High Court today, after being denied his freedom because authorities say he won't reveal where they can find the body of his stepdaughter.

title.children: Double murderer to challenge 'no body, no parole' law in High Court

image.altText: Hail on the grass in Weston Creek

props.synopsis: Canberra residents are recovering this morning after a severe thunderstorm made its way across much of the ACT and surrounding regions yesterday afternoon, knocking out power to around 1,100 households with golf ball sized hailstones and downfalls of 30 millimetres recorded in some suburbs.

title.children: Severe thunderstorm damages roofs, skylights, trees across Canberra

image.altText: Donald Trump meets with Israel's Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu in the Oval Office of the White House.

props.synopsis: US President Donald Trump has signed an executive order imposing sanctions on the ICC over its investigations of Israel, a close US ally — a move that coincides with a visit by Israeli PM Benjamin Netanyahu, who is wanted by the court over the war in Gaza.

title.children: Trump sanctions International Criminal Court, tries to fire election commissioner

image.altText: Australia batters Travis Head and Usman Khawaja walk out during a Test in Galle.

props.synopsis: Australia's batters get their turn on the Galle pitch after Matthew Kuhnemann takes the final Sri Lankan wicket after some frustration early on day two of the second Test. Follow live.

title.children: Last wicket adds valuable runs before Sri Lanka bowled out for 257

image.altText: Max King stands with his hands on his hips

props.synopsis: Max King, Jack Sinclair and Mason Wood have all suffered injuries and been sent for scans after a training session at St Kilda.

title.children: Training ground carnage as Saints trio injured

image.altText: Two men are walking in from of shattered concrete, one with a blue gas tank on his right shoulder and one with a bag.

props.synopsis: Israel's defence minister, Israel Katz, tells the country's military to form plans that allow Palestinians the freedom to leave Gaza.

title.children: Trump doubles down on Gaza proposal, as Israel plans for Palestinians to 'emigrate'

image.altText: A golden pager mounted on a wooden plinth with an inscription from Benjamin Netanyahu to Donald Trump .

props.synopsis: The gift is the latest sign of the close ties between the US and Israel, which used exploding pagers to target Hezbollah personnel in the lead-up to last year's invasion of Lebanon.

title.children: Israeli PM gifts Trump gold pager, in apparent reference to attacks on Hezbollah

image.altText: Robbie Williams hits the red carpet in a black suit

props.synopsis: The red carpet has been rolled out on the Gold Coast for stars including Robbie Williams, Henry Cavill and Miranda Otto to celebrate our homegrown film industry.

title.children: AACTAs 2025 red carpet: Robbie Williams, Sophie Wilde among early arrivals

image.altText: Dominos Pizza store with delivery bicycle outside

props.synopsis: Pizza chain Domino's says it will shut more than 200 loss-making stores, mostly in Japan. The ASX ends the day on a marginal loss. See how the day unfolded with our business reporters on the ABC News live markets blog.

title.children: Domino's Pizza shares surge 20pc on 200 store closures, ASX dips - as it happened

image.altText: Journalists come up with plan to stop job cuts at the Newcastle Herald and Illawarra Mercury.

props.synopsis: Australian Community Media plans to move all mastheads, including Newcastle Herald and Canberra Times, to one print publication a week as it adapts a new publishing model.

title.children: Newspaper publisher ACM plans to cut all mastheads to one print edition per week

image.altText: A masked person holding a sledgehammer and a head severed from a statue.

props.synopsis: Police say images circulating online that appear to show busts of past prime ministers stolen from Ballarat Botanical Gardens indicate the "thinking capacity" of those responsible is "fairly low-end".

title.children: Vandal photographed with head severed from statue of PM

image.altText: The front of the Jewish Museum and War Memorial.

props.synopsis: A magistrate describes the alleged display of a flag with a Nazi swastika near Sydney's Jewish Museum and War Memorial as "disgraceful, disgusting and abhorrent".

title.children: Men accused of 'disgraceful' display of Nazi flag near Sydney Jewish Museum

props.synopsis: Around-the-clock coverage of news events as they break, at home and abroad.

title.children: Watch: News Channel

image.altText: A bald man wearing a suit and tie

props.synopsis: Outgoing ABC chief content officer Chris Oliver-Taylor has claimed he didn't know radio presenter Antoinette Lattouf's race before her alleged unlawful termination, despite sending an email detailing her Lebanese background to the broadcaster's managing director, a court has heard.

title.children: ABC executive says he felt 'pressure from above' before Lattouf's radio exit

image.altText: Brown water with a boat going past what looks like the roof of a pagola.

title.children: BOM issues severe weather warning for flood-stricken north Queensland

image.altText: Houses sitting in floodwaters.

props.synopsis: North Queensland's housing market was already tight before the floods, leaving industry experts worried about finding accommodation for people whose homes are damaged.

title.children: Fears lack of rentals could leave flood-displaced residents in hotels

image.altText: A mid-shot of Ben Dawkins sitting in WA's Legislative Council looking up to his left.

props.synopsis: An analyst says Ben Dawkins's name change to Austin Trump is an "effective" publicity stunt and a potential vote winner.

title.children: Outcast WA politician changes name to 'Aussie' Trump ahead of state election

image.altText: Minister Rose Jackson, with a political poster of NSW Premier Chris Minns behind her.

props.synopsis: While Rose Jackson has conceded the birthday lunch that helped trigger Jo Haylen's resignation was a mistake, the NSW mental health minister still has enough on her plate to worry about: the mass exit of the state's psychiatrists.

title.children: Why Jackson’s ill-advised long lunch could be the least of her worries

image.altText: Close up of some long grass at sunset, silhouetted by rays of light.

props.synopsis: Temperatures have sat in the mid-to-high 40s for most of the week across the Pilbara and Gascoyne with little relief in sight.

title.children: Severe heatwave persists in WA as 50C an outside chance

image.altText: Large plumes of smoke rise from a fire burning across scrub land.

props.synopsis: The CFS says the fire poses no threat to life or property but has issued an advice message for people in the area to monitor conditions and stay informed.

image.altText: A young woman is taking a selfie with her two young kids and her husband.

image.altText: A man in a yellow AFL jersey running holding an AFL ball.

props.synopsis: Foxtel apologises after inadvertently telling subscribers their services will be cut, but others are not so lucky.

title.children: Dozens of postcodes across Australia soon won't have access to Kayo and Binge

image.altText: A headshot of a man with long, silvery hair.

props.synopsis: Police are scouring dense bushland for a gunman wanted over an attempted murder in Tallebudgera Valley yesterday.

title.children: Police hunt for fugitive after homemade gun used in Gold Coast shooting

image.altText: A street lined by buildings

props.synopsis: A man who shot another man through a front door during an attempted home robbery has been sentenced, with the judge describing it as a "tragic" case for all involved.

title.children: Man jailed for 14 years over 'cowardly' murder during failed home robbery

image.altText: A bucket of black snakes.

props.synopsis: More than 100 venomous snakes have been captured in a backyard in Sydney's west in what snake catchers said was their biggest find ever.

title.children: Nest of 102 venomous snakes discovered in Sydney backyard

image.altText: A calendar graphic showing a potential election date and key dates.

props.synopsis: Trying to guess the election date before the prime minister reveals his thinking is always a somewhat futile exercise, but that has never got in the way of feverish speculation throughout the press gallery and beyond.

title.children: It's a federal election year. So when will the election actually be held?

image.altText: Chappell Roan performs during the 67th Annual Grammy Awards.

props.synopsis: Have you been paying attention to the news this week? Let's see what you've got.

title.children: Weekly news quiz: Chappell's award plea, one big bear, and how Putricia smells

image.altText: A drone view of a town in Santorini, Greece, with white buildings with blue roofs, overlooking the Aegean Sea.

props.synopsis: A 5.2 magnitude tremor has been detected between the Greek islands of Santorini and Amorgos — the most powerful recorded since activity started on on January 31.

title.children: Greek government declares state of emergency as earthquakes shake Santorini

image.altText: An older man wearing a rugby jumper stands outside smiling.
